The paper deals with the properties of spatial correlation matrices in wireless communication scenarios, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on massive MIMO systems, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.MM) that deals with large-scale antenna arrays. Finally, the paper presents new bounds on the extreme eigenvalues of the spatial correlation matrix, which is a topic that falls under linear algebra (cs.LG).
